      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Windows updates primarily download patches, drivers, and IoT telemetry to improve system stability and security, not to harvest neural data. While high CPU usage during large updates is normal due to system-wide installation processes, sending raw neural pattern data would require surmounting significant technical and ethical barriers that currently don't exist for consumer operating systems. It is far more likely that the heavy activity represents standard background cache clearing or feature updates rather than any form of biological data mapping. You should verify the specific update source and check for unnecessary third-party apps rather than assuming malicious code, as Windows does perform significant system maintenance even when idle.",
