      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While behavioral data can contribute to advanced AI models, mapping the full complexity of human cognitive processes from keystrokes and mouse movements remains highly improbable with current technology and legal frameworks. The \"technical leap\" requires differentiating intention and distraction, which is far too ambiguous for standard machine learning algorithms to replicate at a human-aware level. It is unlikely that OS updates would act as a primary source for such a massive dataset, as these systems are overwhelmingly focused on hardware compatibility and security patches.",
